description.narrative: 1. Hazardous and Suspected Hazardous Areas assigned by the Libyan Mine Action Center are released in accordance with National Standards to the benefit of the affected community. 2. Awareness of landmines and Explosive Remnants of War-related risks for women, men, girls and boys in contaminated areas is increased through Risk Education. 3. Social inclusion and economic reintegration of victims of landmines and Explosive Remnants of War-related accidents and their families is enhanced. 4. National and community capacity for planning and carrying out mine action activities in the East of Libya, including clearance, risk education and victim assistance is reinforced.
"Enhanced resiliance of vulnerable groups through Improved access to resources, livelihoods and socioeconomic reconstruction"
